## ğŸ”„ DATA FLOW DIAGRAM

```
PATIENT ARRIVAL FLOW:

1. Paramedic Input
   â”œâ”€ Demographics (name, age, gender, blood type)
   â”œâ”€ Medical history (allergies, medications, conditions)
   â”œâ”€ Chief complaint
   â”œâ”€ Vital signs (HR, BP, O2, Temp, RR)
   â”œâ”€ Location (GPS coordinates)
   â””â”€ Destination hospital

2. Data Validation
   â”œâ”€ Field validation (required fields)
   â”œâ”€ Type validation (numeric, string, etc.)
   â”œâ”€ Range validation (HR 40-200 bpm, etc.)
   â””â”€ De-duplication check

3. Encryption
   â”œâ”€ Sensitive data (demographics) â†’ AES-256
   â”œâ”€ Medical history â†’ Encrypted storage
   â””â”€ Transportation â†’ TLS 1.3

4. AI/ML Processing
   â”œâ”€ Triage Classification
   â”‚  â””â”€ Input: Vitals + history â†’ ESI-5 score
   â”œâ”€ Clinical NLP
   â”‚  â””â”€ Extract: Conditions, symptoms, medications
   â””â”€ Risk Scoring
      â””â”€ Output: Mortality, ICU admission probability

5. Record Generation
   â”œâ”€ Parse clinical notes
   â”œâ”€ Convert to ICD-10 codes
   â”œâ”€ Generate structured EHR
   â””â”€ Estimate confidence score

6. Hospital Notification
   â”œâ”€ Create alert record
   â”œâ”€ Determine severity (ESI-1â†’ESI-5)
   â”œâ”€ Route to appropriate departments
   â””â”€ Broadcast via WebSocket

7. Physician Alert
   â”œâ”€ Real-time notification
   â”œâ”€ Pre-generated record display
   â”œâ”€ Team notification
   â””â”€ Resource mobilization

8. Audit Logging
   â”œâ”€ User ID logged
   â”œâ”€ Timestamp recorded
   â”œâ”€ Action documented
   â””â”€ IP address captured

â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
```

