## ğŸ“Š DATABASE SCHEMA

```
DATABASE: ambulink_db

TABLES:

1. users
   â”œâ”€ id (PK)
   â”œâ”€ username (UNIQUE)
   â”œâ”€ email (UNIQUE)
   â”œâ”€ password_hash
   â”œâ”€ role (paramedic, physician, admin)
   â”œâ”€ hospital_id (FK)
   â”œâ”€ ambulance_id
   â”œâ”€ is_active
   â”œâ”€ created_at
   â””â”€ updated_at

2. patients
   â”œâ”€ id (PK)
   â”œâ”€ patient_id (UNIQUE) - PAT-XXXXX
   â”œâ”€ _demographics (ENCRYPTED) - JSON
   â”œâ”€ _medical_history (ENCRYPTED) - JSON
   â”œâ”€ heart_rate
   â”œâ”€ blood_pressure
   â”œâ”€ oxygen_saturation
   â”œâ”€ temperature
   â”œâ”€ respiratory_rate
   â”œâ”€ chief_complaint
   â”œâ”€ triage_level - ESI 1-5
   â”œâ”€ risk_score (0-100)
   â”œâ”€ ambulance_id
   â”œâ”€ origin_latitude
   â”œâ”€ origin_longitude
   â”œâ”€ destination_hospital_id (FK)
   â”œâ”€ estimated_arrival
   â”œâ”€ created_at (INDEX)
   â””â”€ updated_at

3. hospitals
   â”œâ”€ id (PK)
   â”œâ”€ name
   â”œâ”€ latitude
   â”œâ”€ longitude
   â”œâ”€ specialties (JSON array)
   â”œâ”€ bed_capacity
   â”œâ”€ current_occupancy
   â””â”€ is_active

4. alerts
   â”œâ”€ id (PK)
   â”œâ”€ alert_id (UNIQUE) - ALR-XXXXX
   â”œâ”€ patient_id (FK, INDEX)
   â”œâ”€ hospital_id (FK)
   â”œâ”€ alert_type - patient_arrival, high_risk, critical
   â”œâ”€ severity - critical, high, medium, low
   â”œâ”€ message
   â”œâ”€ department
   â”œâ”€ is_acknowledged
   â”œâ”€ acknowledged_by (FK)
